00:10:53.580 --> 00:10:55.390
as we will now be calculating.

00:10:55.390 --> 00:10:57.550
And in the more recent
period, the universe

00:10:57.550 --> 00:10:59.129
is dominated by
dark energy, which

00:10:59.129 --> 00:11:00.920
we'll be talking about
immediately after we

00:11:00.920 --> 00:11:04.090
finish talking about radiation.

00:11:04.090 --> 00:11:08.070
So the important point here is
that even though we don't think

00:11:08.070 --> 00:11:11.220
of light as having
mass, light certainly

00:11:11.220 --> 00:11:13.640
has energy and
relativistically we

00:11:13.640 --> 00:11:16.200
know that energy and
mass are equivalent.

00:11:16.200 --> 00:11:20.470
The key equation that actually
dominates today's lecture

00:11:20.470 --> 00:11:24.610
is perhaps the most
famous equation physics,

00:11:24.610 --> 00:11:30.260
E equals MC squared, energy
and mass are equivalent.

00:11:30.260 --> 00:11:32.689
And the numbers--
I'll just give you

00:11:32.689 --> 00:11:33.980
some numbers for this equation.

00:11:33.980 --> 00:11:35.930
You've probably already
aware that the numbers

00:11:35.930 --> 00:11:38.560
are kind of out of sight.

00:11:38.560 --> 00:11:45.190
One kilogram, a point
to that equation,

00:11:45.190 --> 00:11:50.390
is equivalent to-- I don't
have any figures to give you--

00:11:50.390 --> 00:11:56.860
