it means that if you could
convert one kilogram per hour

00:14:27.910 --> 00:14:31.110
into pure energy,
that would be about

00:14:31.110 --> 00:14:51.680
equal to 1.5 times the
world's power usage in 2008.

00:14:51.680 --> 00:14:55.370
So if you could convert
matter completely to energy,

00:14:55.370 --> 00:14:57.780
as they do on Star
Trek, it would

00:14:57.780 --> 00:14:59.590
mean that you could
fill up your tank

00:14:59.590 --> 00:15:03.290
of your typical
American car and power

00:15:03.290 --> 00:15:04.515
the world for about two days.

00:15:07.476 --> 00:15:08.850
But of course we
can't undo this,

00:15:08.850 --> 00:15:12.670
that's the important
fact concerning power.

00:15:12.670 --> 00:15:15.620
Only a small
fraction of the mass

00:15:15.620 --> 00:15:18.010
of the uranium in
a nuclear reactor

00:15:18.010 --> 00:15:22.050
is actually converted as
power, a fraction of a percent.

00:15:22.050 --> 00:15:23.730
So you don't get
nearly as much power

00:15:23.730 --> 00:15:25.340
as this calculation
would indicate,

00:15:25.340 --> 00:15:26.790
but in principle
this much energy

00:15:26.790 --> 00:15:31.620
is contained in the matter that
we have around us all the time.

00:15:49.730 --> 00:15:50.230
OK.

00:15:50.230 --> 00:15:51.896
I want to introduce
a few formulas which

00:15:51.896 --> 00:15:53.660
we'll be using sooner
or later concerning

00:15:53.660 --> 00:15:57.190
the relativistic treatment
of momentum and energy,

00:15:57.190 --> 00:15:58.940
which is what we're
getting into here.

00:15:58.940 --> 00:16:03.070
And we're not trying to derive
relativity in this course,

00:16:03.070 --> 00:16:07.110
so I'm just trying to quote the
results that we'll be needing.

00:16:07.110 --> 00:16:16.910
So, it is useful to introduce
an energy momentum four-vector,

00:16:16.910 --> 00:16:22.680
which has a 0-th component
and an i-th component,

00:16:22.680 --> 00:16:27.280
where i refers to the
spatial indices 1, 2, and 3.

00:16:27.280 --> 00:16:32.130
And sometimes I might
write this as p zero p

00:16:32.130 --> 00:16:35.050
with a vector sign over it,
where the vector sign indicates

00:16:35.050 --> 00:16:36.750
the three components 1, 2, 3.

00:16:39.610 --> 00:16:43.340
The momentum here
is the momentum.

00:16:43.340 --> 00:16:45.415
It differs in its
relationship to velocity

00:16:45.415 --> 00:16:47.040
from what we have
from Newton, and I'll

00:16:47.040 --> 00:16:48.880
write that in a minute,
but this momentum

00:16:48.880 --> 00:16:52.330
is the conserved physical
momentum of an object.

00:16:52.330 --> 00:16:55.080
And p0 is also conserved.

00:16:55.080 --> 00:17:05.140
p0 is just an abbreviation
for the energy divided by C.

00:17:05.140 --> 00:17:07.630
And this quantity forms
a four dimensional

00:17:07.630 --> 00:17:09.530
vector in special relativity.

00:17:09.530 --> 00:17:11.589
And when we say that
it's a four-vector,

00:17:11.589 --> 00:17:13.609
we're actually making
a definite statement

00:17:13.609 --> 00:17:17.519
about how it transforms from
one Lorentz frame to another.

00:17:17.519 --> 00:17:20.190
a four-vector is
something which transforms

00:17:20.190 --> 00:17:24.890
in exactly the same way as x
super mu, four spatial and time

00:17:24.890 --> 00:17:25.975
coordinates transform.

00:17:29.140 --> 00:17:31.410
And in particular,
we learned that there

00:17:31.410 --> 00:17:35.040
was an invariant associated with
spacetime transformations this

00:17:35.040 --> 00:17:38.530
s squared, which was x squared
plus y squared plus z squared

00:17:38.530 --> 00:17:41.150
minus C squared t squared.

00:17:41.150 --> 00:17:45.170
And the same thing
will happen here.

00:17:45.170 --> 00:17:56.270
p squared, which means
the Lorentz invariant

00:17:56.270 --> 00:18:08.000
square of the four-vector is the
Lorentz [INAUDIBLE] again here,

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:12.880
and it's again equal to the
sum of the squares of the 3

00:18:12.880 --> 00:18:19.450
spatial components minus the
square of the time component.

00:18:24.790 --> 00:18:34.280
And that can be written out as
the square of the momentum--

00:18:34.280 --> 00:18:38.000
spatial momentum-- minus
E squared C squared.

00:18:42.460 --> 00:18:44.925
And the claim is that this
is also Lorentz invariant.

00:19:01.990 --> 00:19:04.670
And we could figure out what
Lorentz invariant quantity

00:19:04.670 --> 00:19:08.511
it's equal to by
having knowledge

00:19:08.511 --> 00:19:10.010
that this is the
same in all frames.

00:19:10.010 --> 00:19:12.550
We can evaluate it in
the simplest frame.

00:19:12.550 --> 00:19:15.165
And the simplest frame would be
the rest frame of the object.

00:19:15.165 --> 00:19:17.290
In the rest frame of the
object the p would be zero

00:19:17.290 --> 00:19:20.670
and this would then just be
minus E squared over C squared.

00:19:20.670 --> 00:19:25.800
E squared would be M
squared C to the fourth,

00:19:25.800 --> 00:19:36.810
so that implies that this is
equal to minus M0 C squared

00:19:36.810 --> 00:19:43.960
squared where M0 is often
called the rest mass.

00:19:49.670 --> 00:19:53.030
And when I say it's often called
the the rest mass, what I mean

00:19:53.030 --> 00:19:54.950
is that nobody ever
mistakes the word "rest

00:19:54.950 --> 00:19:57.840
mass" to mean anything else,
if anybody says "rest mass,"

00:19:57.840 --> 00:20:00.150
and he knows what he's
talking about, he means this.

00:20:00.150 --> 00:20:02.230
But this is often sometimes
just called the mass

00:20:02.230 --> 00:20:04.440
because sometimes people
only talk about masses

00:20:04.440 --> 00:20:06.714
as being rest masses.

00:20:06.714 --> 00:20:08.130
But I'll try to
call this the rest

00:20:08.130 --> 00:20:10.780
mass because I will use the
word mass in other ways.

00:20:19.490 --> 00:20:23.130
We could also relate this
momentum to the velocity,

00:20:23.130 --> 00:20:27.220
and in doing that we will again
encounter this factor of gamma

00:20:27.220 --> 00:20:29.900
that we found
kinematically earlier.

00:20:29.900 --> 00:20:31.083
AUDIENCE: Yes, question.

00:20:31.083 --> 00:20:34.190
Did you forget to divide
by C squared there?

00:20:34.190 --> 00:20:42.420
PROFESSOR: Um, yes.

00:20:42.420 --> 00:20:45.330
There's too many C's here.

00:20:45.330 --> 00:20:46.220
Absolutely.

00:20:46.220 --> 00:20:48.380
It should have
units of momentum.

00:20:48.380 --> 00:20:52.030
So it should have units of
mass times velocity squared.

00:20:52.030 --> 00:20:52.920
Thank you.

00:20:52.920 --> 00:20:53.420
Thank you.

00:20:59.030 --> 00:21:04.769
So, the quantity gamma,
is the same quantity

00:21:04.769 --> 00:21:06.560
we encounter at the
beginning of the course

00:21:06.560 --> 00:21:08.650
when we talked about
time dilation and Lorentz

00:21:08.650 --> 00:21:12.070
contraction, it just depends
on the velocity and approaches

00:21:12.070 --> 00:21:14.830
infinity as the velocity
approaches the speed of light.

00:21:14.830 --> 00:21:19.360
And the physical momentum of
a particle, relativistically

00:21:19.360 --> 00:21:23.750
is equal to gamma
times M sub 0 times V.

00:21:23.750 --> 00:21:27.421
Where V is the ordinary
velocity-- this

00:21:27.421 --> 00:21:29.170
is special relativity,
we're not concerned

00:21:29.170 --> 00:21:32.800
with coordinate velocity
versus physical velocity yet--

00:21:32.800 --> 00:21:34.920
and gamma is that factor.

00:21:34.920 --> 00:21:39.040
So the momentum is larger than
what you would get a la Newton.

00:21:39.040 --> 00:21:43.260
The energy can also
be written down.

00:21:43.260 --> 00:21:48.480
And this formula
is one expression

00:21:48.480 --> 00:21:51.285
we can use to find the energy
in terms of the momentum.

00:21:59.380 --> 00:22:04.570
The energy in terms
of the momentum

00:22:04.570 --> 00:22:15.420
is M0 C squared squared
plus p squared C squared.

00:22:15.420 --> 00:22:18.830
And it also can be written
in terms of the velocity

00:22:18.830 --> 00:22:22.610
as just gamma times M0 C squared
where the velocity appears

00:22:22.610 --> 00:22:23.220
in the gamma.

00:22:39.390 --> 00:22:44.430
And a special case of this is
when the particle is at rest.

00:22:44.430 --> 00:22:49.660
Might as well write this, the
energy of a particle at rest,

00:22:49.660 --> 00:22:54.180
which we might call E0, is just
M0 C squared, which gets us

00:22:54.180 --> 00:22:58.350
back to where we started
with E equals MC squared.

00:23:01.624 --> 00:23:03.040
Now, I might just
say a quick word

00:23:03.040 --> 00:23:05.946
about where these formulas come
from, what idea underlies them.

00:23:05.946 --> 00:23:07.320
I'm not going to
make any attempt

00:23:07.320 --> 00:23:10.080
to derive them because
we just don't have time.

00:23:10.080 --> 00:23:13.510
It'd be easy to drive them,
but we want to do other things.

00:23:13.510 --> 00:23:15.550
But logically,
where they come from

00:23:15.550 --> 00:23:20.650
is simply the observation,
by Einstein originally,

00:23:20.650 --> 00:23:24.290
that if one has the Lorentz
transformations relating

00:23:24.290 --> 00:23:29.260
what one inertial observer sees
to another inertial observer,

00:23:29.260 --> 00:23:32.425
if one used those
transformations but used

00:23:32.425 --> 00:23:35.820
the Newtonian definitions
of energy and momentum,

00:23:35.820 --> 00:23:38.430
then you would find immediately
that if energy and momentum

00:23:38.430 --> 00:23:41.770
were conserved in one frame you
then know how to calculate what

00:23:41.770 --> 00:23:44.210
happens in other frames by
using the transformations,

00:23:44.210 --> 00:23:47.220
you'd find it would not
be conserved other frames.

00:23:47.220 --> 00:23:49.710
So if the conservation
of energy and momentum

00:23:49.710 --> 00:23:53.150
are to be a universal principle
of physics, which Einstein

00:23:53.150 --> 00:23:57.080
wanted to maintain, it would
be necessary to redefine

00:23:57.080 --> 00:23:58.630
energy and momentum.

00:23:58.630 --> 00:24:01.220
Now they're defined in
ways so that they approach

00:24:01.220 --> 00:24:04.110
the Newtonian values
for small velocities,

00:24:04.110 --> 00:24:07.030
but for velocities of the
order of the speed of light

00:24:07.030 --> 00:24:08.000
they're different.

00:24:08.000 --> 00:24:10.734
And they have the property--
not completely obvious from what

00:24:10.734 --> 00:24:13.150
we wrote, well it is actually
completely obvious from what

00:24:13.150 --> 00:24:14.780
we wrote-- they
have the property

00:24:14.780 --> 00:24:17.770
that if it's
conserved in on frame,

00:24:17.770 --> 00:24:19.420
it's conserved in all frames.

00:24:19.420 --> 00:24:21.291
And what makes it
obvious-- maybe

00:24:21.291 --> 00:24:23.290
the connections between
these different formulas

00:24:23.290 --> 00:24:25.400
are not obvious--
but I did tell you

00:24:25.400 --> 00:24:29.900
that p super mu transforms
as a four-vector,

00:24:29.900 --> 00:24:33.100
meaning it transforms the same
way as x super mu transforms,

00:24:33.100 --> 00:24:35.030
which are linear
transformations.

00:24:35.030 --> 00:24:38.517
And that's enough to guarantee
that if p mu is conserved

00:24:38.517 --> 00:24:40.600
in one frame, it has to
be conserved in all frames

00:24:40.600 --> 00:24:43.210
because delta p mu,
the change in p mu,

00:24:43.210 --> 00:24:45.815
would also be a four-vector,
and if a four-vector vanishes

00:24:45.815 --> 00:24:47.705
in one frame, it
vanishes in all frames.

00:24:56.940 --> 00:24:57.440
OK.

00:24:57.440 --> 00:24:59.773
Well I wanted to give you
sort of a quick example of how

00:24:59.773 --> 00:25:00.925
this works in practice.

00:25:13.170 --> 00:25:15.775
So I to just talk about the
energetics of a hydrogen atom.

00:25:25.770 --> 00:25:30.820
A hydrogen atom
consists of a proton,

00:25:30.820 --> 00:25:38.582
with a mass that we'll call
M sub p, and an electron,

00:25:38.582 --> 00:25:40.040
with the mass that
we'll call M sub

00:25:40.040 --> 00:25:46.680
E. And, as, if you imagine
starting with the electron

00:25:46.680 --> 00:25:50.890
and proton arbitrarily far
apart and bring them together,

00:25:50.890 --> 00:25:53.492
what you can discover
experimentally-- of if you know

00:25:53.492 --> 00:25:54.950
quantum mechanics
you can calculate

00:25:54.950 --> 00:25:58.960
theoretically--
energy is released,

00:25:58.960 --> 00:26:01.160
because you're releasing
potential energy as you

00:26:01.160 --> 00:26:03.430
bring the electron
into the atom.

00:26:03.430 --> 00:26:08.490
And the amount of
energy released

00:26:08.490 --> 00:26:20.070
is 13.6 electron volts.

00:26:20.070 --> 00:26:22.220
And the important
E equals MC squared

00:26:22.220 --> 00:26:24.010
implication which I
want to point out here

00:26:24.010 --> 00:26:26.544
is that loss of energy.

00:26:26.544 --> 00:26:28.460
This energy would be
extracted from the system

00:26:28.460 --> 00:26:30.192
as you made the hydrogen atom.

00:26:30.192 --> 00:26:32.400
The fact that you've extracted
energy from the system

00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:34.530
means that now the system
should have less energy

00:26:34.530 --> 00:26:36.314
than it had to start with.

00:26:36.314 --> 00:26:38.230
Initially it had the
rest energy of the proton

00:26:38.230 --> 00:26:42.760
and the rest of electronic, M
sub p C squared and M sub E C

00:26:42.760 --> 00:26:43.620
squared.

00:26:43.620 --> 00:26:45.530
Now it has less
energy by delta E,

00:26:45.530 --> 00:26:48.250
and that means it also
has to have less mass.

00:26:48.250 --> 00:26:50.120
So the mass of a
hydrogen atom is not

00:26:50.120 --> 00:26:52.190
the sum of the mass of
the proton and electron,

00:26:52.190 --> 00:26:54.300
as it would be in
Newtonian mechanics,

00:26:54.300 --> 00:26:56.940
but is less by an
amount proportional

00:26:56.940 --> 00:27:01.717
to this energy given off,
delta E, 13.6 electron volts.

00:27:01.717 --> 00:27:03.300
And just putting in
the C squares in I

00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:07.120
hope the right places, the
mass of a hydrogen atom

00:27:07.120 --> 00:27:09.780
will be equal to
the mass of a proton

00:27:09.780 --> 00:27:12.040
plus the mass of an
electron, but then

00:27:12.040 --> 00:27:18.800
minus the binding energy
expressed in mass units-- delta

00:27:18.800 --> 00:27:19.760
E over C squared.

00:27:36.420 --> 00:27:36.920
OK.

00:27:36.920 --> 00:27:38.900
So I guess, just
probably one more topic

00:27:38.900 --> 00:27:41.940
I want to talk about in terms of
just basic special relativity,

00:27:41.940 --> 00:27:45.840
and this actually get's
into general relativity.

00:27:45.840 --> 00:27:48.190
I wanted to find the
relativistic mass

00:27:48.190 --> 00:27:53.570
of any system just being its
energy divided by C squared.

00:27:58.970 --> 00:28:01.310
And this means that the
relativistic mass of a particle

00:28:01.310 --> 00:28:03.960
increases with its velocity.

00:28:03.960 --> 00:28:06.060
The energy of a
single moving particle

00:28:06.060 --> 00:28:08.280
is gamma times M0 C squared.

00:28:08.280 --> 00:28:09.940
That would say the
by this definition

00:28:09.940 --> 00:28:15.390
the relativistic mass of that
particle is gamma times M0.

00:28:15.390 --> 00:28:18.390
And I might mention that this
concept of relativistic mass

00:28:18.390 --> 00:28:22.410
is disparaged in many books
on special relativity.

00:28:22.410 --> 00:28:24.650
It's certainly a concept
that you can do without,

00:28:24.650 --> 00:28:27.840
so people who emotionally
are bothered by it

00:28:27.840 --> 00:28:29.720
can get along without
it because it is just

00:28:29.720 --> 00:28:31.350
the energy divided by C squared.

00:28:31.350 --> 00:28:34.750
And in fact a lot of work
in special relativity

00:28:34.750 --> 00:28:37.150
is done in units
where C is equal to 1

00:28:37.150 --> 00:28:39.060
and then it is just the energy.

00:28:39.060 --> 00:28:41.000
Especially if you
use C equals 1 you

00:28:41.000 --> 00:28:44.245
could dispense with this
concept of relativistic mass.

00:28:44.245 --> 00:28:45.870
We're not going to
be using C equals 1,

00:28:45.870 --> 00:28:48.940
so the phrase
relativistic mass will

00:28:48.940 --> 00:28:50.650
allow us to abbreviate
E divided by E

00:28:50.650 --> 00:28:53.460
squared in a convenient way.

00:28:53.460 --> 00:28:55.650
But the important thing
is not the definitions,

00:28:55.650 --> 00:28:57.233
the important thing
is what properties

00:28:57.233 --> 00:28:59.400
does this relativistic
mass have,

00:28:59.400 --> 00:29:01.710
whether or not one chooses
to call it relativistic mass

00:29:01.710 --> 00:29:03.920
or E divided by C squared.

00:29:03.920 --> 00:29:07.030
And it as an important
property concerning

00:29:07.030 --> 00:29:10.980
the gravitational field
created by matter.

00:29:10.980 --> 00:29:15.420
Now the gravitational field
of a single moving object

00:29:15.420 --> 00:29:17.130
is complicated.

00:29:17.130 --> 00:29:19.880
If we were talking
about, say, a moving star

00:29:19.880 --> 00:29:22.440
that was moving at a
velocity large enough

00:29:22.440 --> 00:29:26.947
so we care about relativity, the
way we calculate that actually

00:29:26.947 --> 00:29:28.947
as we start with the
Schwarzschild metric, which

00:29:28.947 --> 00:29:32.190
will describe the metric of
the star outside of the matter

00:29:32.190 --> 00:29:33.310
if it were stationary.

00:29:33.310 --> 00:29:35.101
And then you can just
make a transformation

00:29:35.101 --> 00:29:35.960
to a moving frame.

00:29:35.960 --> 00:29:37.501
You're allowed to
use any coordinates

00:29:37.501 --> 00:29:39.730
you want in general
relativity, so transforming

00:29:39.730 --> 00:29:43.680
to coordinates that describe
the moving frame is no problem.

00:29:43.680 --> 00:29:47.480
But it distorts the field in a
complicated way, nonetheless,

00:29:47.480 --> 00:29:49.330
a way that you can deal with.

00:29:51.940 --> 00:29:53.690
And what you find, of
course, is that what

00:29:53.690 --> 00:29:56.590
you get would be asymmetric
once you transform to the moving

00:29:56.590 --> 00:30:00.520
frame, it would show the
signs of the velocity

00:30:00.520 --> 00:30:03.500
that you used to transform
from the original spherically

00:30:03.500 --> 00:30:06.597
symmetric Schwarzschild
metric to the new frame.

00:30:06.597 --> 00:30:09.180
So the bottom line is that the
gravitational field of a moving

00:30:09.180 --> 00:30:13.330
object is not isotropic, it's
more complicated than that,

00:30:13.330 --> 00:30:16.310
just as the electric
field would be.

00:30:16.310 --> 00:30:19.860
But if we have a
gas of particles,

00:30:19.860 --> 00:30:24.160
which is pretty much what we
have in the early universe.

00:30:24.160 --> 00:30:35.290
If we have a gas of particles
in a box moving every which way,

00:30:35.290 --> 00:30:38.575
then if we thought of this
box as being an object

00:30:38.575 --> 00:30:40.700
that we're only going to
look at from the outside--

00:30:40.700 --> 00:30:43.880
a black box in the
classic use of the phrase

00:30:43.880 --> 00:30:51.320
black box-- the mass
of the black box

00:30:51.320 --> 00:30:56.352
really would just be the sum
of the relativistic masses

00:30:56.352 --> 00:30:57.060
of the particles.

00:31:00.250 --> 00:31:05.300
And the isotropy of the metric
that any one particle would

00:31:05.300 --> 00:31:08.670
generate would be canceled
by averaging or summing

00:31:08.670 --> 00:31:11.230
over all the particles going
every which direction, because

00:31:11.230 --> 00:31:17.162
on average the velocity of
particles inside the box is 0.

00:31:17.162 --> 00:31:19.620
So this relativistic mass, when
you're talking about a gas,

00:31:19.620 --> 00:31:22.780
really is the mass per particle.

00:31:22.780 --> 00:31:24.970
And if you divide
that by the volume

00:31:24.970 --> 00:31:26.820
really you do get
the mass density,

00:31:26.820 --> 00:31:28.720
which is a relevant
mass density in terms

00:31:28.720 --> 00:31:30.960
of talking about how
this matter would

00:31:30.960 --> 00:31:33.300
generate gravitational fields.

00:31:33.300 --> 00:31:33.800
Yes.

00:31:33.800 --> 00:31:35.299
AUDIENCE: So why
do some people have

00:31:35.299 --> 00:31:37.447
emotional problems with it?

00:31:37.447 --> 00:31:40.030
PROFESSOR: I think some people
have emotional problems with it

00:31:40.030 --> 00:31:42.860
because when one thinks
about pedagogy in a course,

00:31:42.860 --> 00:31:45.900
for example, one worries
about people confusing it

00:31:45.900 --> 00:31:49.067
with the rest mass.

00:31:49.067 --> 00:31:50.150
I think that's the reason.

00:31:54.390 --> 00:31:56.950
And I guess there are other
possible sources of confusion,

00:31:56.950 --> 00:31:59.020
so your question is a good one.

00:31:59.020 --> 00:32:02.340
Another source of confusion
is that this mass does not

00:32:02.340 --> 00:32:04.679
fit into an F
equals ma equation.

00:32:04.679 --> 00:32:06.220
So in calling this
the mass you might

00:32:06.220 --> 00:32:09.920
suggest to students who aren't
paying attention to every word

00:32:09.920 --> 00:32:12.880
that you say, you might
go ahead and put F equals

00:32:12.880 --> 00:32:14.440
ma for this mass,
that does not work.

00:32:18.420 --> 00:32:20.600
So it has some of the
properties of a mass,

00:32:20.600 --> 00:32:22.369
but not-- by no
means all of them.

00:32:27.719 --> 00:32:29.260
But in particular
for us is important

00:32:29.260 --> 00:32:31.634
because we're going to be
interested in the gravitational

00:32:31.634 --> 00:32:33.710
field of a gas
and then it really

00:32:33.710 --> 00:32:35.730
is the mass that
determines that.

00:32:40.640 --> 00:32:42.950
In the more formal language
in general relativity,

00:32:42.950 --> 00:32:46.182
it's the mass-- it's
the energy density, that

00:32:46.182 --> 00:32:48.640
appears in the equations that
produce gravitational fields,

00:32:48.640 --> 00:32:50.395
and then this really
is the energy density

00:32:50.395 --> 00:32:54.230
except for a factor
of C squared.

00:32:54.230 --> 00:32:55.020
OK, any questions?

00:32:55.020 --> 00:32:57.680
Because now I'm going
to leave this formalism

00:32:57.680 --> 00:33:02.921
and get into what role
this radiation could

00:33:02.921 --> 00:33:04.045
play in the early universe.

00:33:32.800 --> 00:33:37.106
So now I'd like to talk about
radiation in particular,

00:33:37.106 --> 00:33:39.450
and for now I mean
electromagnetic radiation

00:33:39.450 --> 00:33:42.530
just ordinary photons.

00:33:42.530 --> 00:33:46.330
And we're not accustomed
to thinking of light

00:33:46.330 --> 00:33:47.980
as having mass,
but we know light

00:33:47.980 --> 00:33:51.740
has energy and energy is
related to mass by a factor of C

00:33:51.740 --> 00:33:52.560
squared.

00:33:52.560 --> 00:33:57.000
So we can write down
the formula that

00:33:57.000 --> 00:34:01.330
says that rho is equal to
u divided by C squared.

00:34:01.330 --> 00:34:02.940
Where u is the
energy density, which

00:34:02.940 --> 00:34:04.525
we know electromagnetic
fields have.

00:34:10.699 --> 00:34:13.670
And rho will be the mass
density of radiation.

00:34:52.710 --> 00:34:57.810
Now, photons have
zero rest mass,

00:34:57.810 --> 00:35:01.630
so if we apply for example
this formula for a photon

00:35:01.630 --> 00:35:04.469
we would set M sub 0 equal to 0.

00:35:04.469 --> 00:35:06.510
And we said that photons
have zero rest mass what

00:35:06.510 --> 00:35:09.930
we mean is that
there's no lower limit

00:35:09.930 --> 00:35:11.961
to the energy a photon can have.

00:35:11.961 --> 00:35:13.460
In general, the
rest mass determines

00:35:13.460 --> 00:35:15.640
the lowest possible energy
a particle could have,

00:35:15.640 --> 00:35:17.020
which is when it's at rest.

00:35:17.020 --> 00:35:19.360
Photon can never
be rest and there's

00:35:19.360 --> 00:35:21.990
no lower limit to what
its energy can be.

00:35:27.350 --> 00:35:36.390
So for photons, M0 is
equal to 0 and that

00:35:36.390 --> 00:35:41.860
implies that the
energy of the photon

00:35:41.860 --> 00:35:44.790
is just C times the
magnitude of its momentum.

00:35:51.372 --> 00:35:53.955
And this formula one can derive
just for electromagnetic waves

00:35:53.955 --> 00:35:56.130
is purely classical
EM-- you don't

00:35:56.130 --> 00:35:58.057
have to be talking
about photons,

00:35:58.057 --> 00:36:00.390
but since it's true for a
classical electromagnetic wave

00:36:00.390 --> 00:36:02.890
it had better also be true
for photons because we think

00:36:02.890 --> 00:36:05.210
of this classical
electromagnetic waves

00:36:05.210 --> 00:36:09.340
as really being
made out of photons.

00:36:09.340 --> 00:36:11.520
So the energy that
exists in the universe

00:36:11.520 --> 00:36:13.970
in the form of
electromagnetic radiation

00:36:13.970 --> 00:36:18.230
will have an energy density,
which we know how to calculate.

00:36:18.230 --> 00:36:21.540
And we know to calculate the
momentum of any given photon.

00:36:21.540 --> 00:36:24.260
Now that will average
to zero, but nonetheless

00:36:24.260 --> 00:36:28.010
if we imagine talking about
a box of photons, which

00:36:28.010 --> 00:36:29.745
are bouncing off
the walls, the fact

00:36:29.745 --> 00:36:31.120
that each photon
carries momentum

00:36:31.120 --> 00:36:34.030
means that there will be
a pressure on the walls.

00:36:34.030 --> 00:36:36.450
And we will be interested
in that pressure,

00:36:36.450 --> 00:36:40.040
we'll be calculating a
formula for it in a minute.

00:36:40.040 --> 00:36:42.910
So, what we now
want to talk about

00:36:42.910 --> 00:36:48.555
is what happens when we put a
photon gas into the universe

00:36:48.555 --> 00:36:49.930
and allow the
universe to expand.

00:37:24.326 --> 00:37:26.200
What happens to the
radiation energy density,

00:37:26.200 --> 00:37:29.960
or equivalently mass density,
as the universe expands?

00:37:35.860 --> 00:37:38.260
This turns out to be
a very easy question

00:37:38.260 --> 00:37:40.770
to answer if we
think of the energy

00:37:40.770 --> 00:37:43.960
as being made out of photons.

00:37:43.960 --> 00:37:47.690
We would get an equivalent
identical answer

00:37:47.690 --> 00:37:52.057
if we use classical
Maxwell's equations

00:37:52.057 --> 00:37:53.640
and talked about how
energy density is

00:37:53.640 --> 00:37:55.954
a [INAUDIBLE] of
electromagnetic fields behaved.

00:37:55.954 --> 00:37:57.870
It would be more work
actually do it that way,

00:37:57.870 --> 00:38:00.140
but we would get
the same answer.

00:38:00.140 --> 00:38:02.210
In terms of photos,
we could simply

00:38:02.210 --> 00:38:09.010
notice that the number
density of photons-- photons

00:38:09.010 --> 00:38:11.690
are not going to disappear
as the universe expands,

00:38:11.690 --> 00:38:13.350
the number density
will just keep

00:38:13.350 --> 00:38:16.160
the same number of photons,
but as the universe expands

00:38:16.160 --> 00:38:19.172
those photons will
occupy a larger volume.

00:38:19.172 --> 00:38:20.630
So it's exactly
the same as what we

00:38:20.630 --> 00:38:23.380
said about
non-relativistic matter,

00:38:23.380 --> 00:38:26.840
the number density of
photons will fall like 1

00:38:26.840 --> 00:38:31.380
over the cube of the
scale factor, which just

00:38:31.380 --> 00:38:33.035
says that photons are conserved.

00:38:41.200 --> 00:38:46.520
And the volume of any
region grows like a cubed.

00:38:46.520 --> 00:38:49.477
I should also mention
that I'm using gamma here.

00:38:49.477 --> 00:38:51.060
Gamma of course also
sometimes meant 1

00:38:51.060 --> 00:38:53.435
over the square-root of 1
minus V squared over C squared,

00:38:53.435 --> 00:38:55.570
but besides that
use, gamma is also

00:38:55.570 --> 00:38:57.340
just a label that means photons.

00:39:00.920 --> 00:39:02.820
It comes from the
idea of gamma rays,

00:39:02.820 --> 00:39:05.180
but it's actually
used in this context

00:39:05.180 --> 00:39:08.092
for any kind of a
photon no matter

00:39:08.092 --> 00:39:09.550
what its frequency
is, whether it's

00:39:09.550 --> 00:39:13.010
a gamma ray or an x-ray or
visible light, or infrared.

00:39:13.010 --> 00:39:13.510
Yes.

00:39:13.510 --> 00:39:15.930
AUDIENCE: Is this
assumed for time average?

00:39:15.930 --> 00:39:18.350
Because photons can
be absorbed, right?

00:39:18.350 --> 00:39:20.286
I mean, at least like
in a small [? slice ?]

00:39:20.286 --> 00:39:23.680
can't there be a decided
non-relativistic matter?

00:39:23.680 --> 00:39:25.090
PROFESSOR: Is this
true on the--?

00:39:25.090 --> 00:39:28.650
Well, the validity of
this formula-- you're

00:39:28.650 --> 00:39:32.130
right this formula's not
exact, photons can be absorbed.

00:39:32.130 --> 00:39:34.940
But in terms of what happens
as the universe evolves,

00:39:34.940 --> 00:39:37.450
that's a very, very,
very minor process,

00:39:37.450 --> 00:39:39.700
especially when we're talking
about the early universe

00:39:39.700 --> 00:39:43.180
when there isn't really
anything around to absorb them.

00:39:43.180 --> 00:39:46.055
So, especially for the early
universe and even pretty well

00:39:46.055 --> 00:39:48.180
today, if we're talking
about the cosmic background

00:39:48.180 --> 00:39:51.380
radiation, which is the
bulk of the photons,

00:39:51.380 --> 00:39:55.390
this formula's a very
good approximation.

00:39:55.390 --> 00:39:55.890
Yes.

00:39:55.890 --> 00:39:59.320
AUDIENCE: Even though the
photons in the early universe

00:39:59.320 --> 00:40:01.280
created a lot of
massive particles,

00:40:01.280 --> 00:40:05.710
[INAUDIBLE] didn't that
affect the expansion?

00:40:05.710 --> 00:40:09.200
PROFESSOR: Are you're
asking, will the photons

00:40:09.200 --> 00:40:11.540
be important if there's a
lot of mass of particles?

00:40:11.540 --> 00:40:12.210
Is that your question?

00:40:12.210 --> 00:40:13.835
AUDIENCE: Would the
photons, won't they

00:40:13.835 --> 00:40:17.060
decay into matter antimatter?

00:40:17.060 --> 00:40:20.040
PROFESSOR: Will the photon
decay into matter antimatter?

00:40:20.040 --> 00:40:22.860
No, not really.

00:40:22.860 --> 00:40:26.670
It is, in principle,
possible for two photons

00:40:26.670 --> 00:40:30.750
to collide and produce an
electron positron pair.

00:40:30.750 --> 00:40:34.700
It's actually a rather small
cross section for that.

00:40:34.700 --> 00:40:38.510
And all of these processes
in the early universe

00:40:38.510 --> 00:40:40.400
will rapidly reach
an equilibrium,

00:40:40.400 --> 00:40:42.880
which we'll be talking about
more a little later, where

00:40:42.880 --> 00:40:45.640
there'll be just as many
photons converting into E plus E

00:40:45.640 --> 00:40:48.700
minus pairs as there will be
E plus E minus pairs colliding

00:40:48.700 --> 00:40:51.220
and making photons.

00:40:51.220 --> 00:40:55.360
So the early universe is
assumed to reach equilibrium

00:40:55.360 --> 00:40:58.817
very quickly, and all the
description we'll be giving

00:40:58.817 --> 00:41:00.650
will be a description
of the universe that's

00:41:00.650 --> 00:41:03.070
in thermal equilibrium
with these processes will

00:41:03.070 --> 00:41:05.110
tend to iron out.

00:41:05.110 --> 00:41:06.610
We will learn that
they don't always

00:41:06.610 --> 00:41:08.693
cancel each other because
the universe is cooling,

00:41:08.693 --> 00:41:11.935
and that means it can't be
exactly in thermal equilibrium.

00:41:11.935 --> 00:41:14.310
And there are some cases where
the effect of that cooling

00:41:14.310 --> 00:41:16.700
is significant and we'll
be talking about those.

00:41:16.700 --> 00:41:18.750
But for the most part,
if the cooling is slow,

00:41:18.750 --> 00:41:22.769
which it is for the most part
compared to other processes,

00:41:22.769 --> 00:41:24.435
everything stays in
thermal equilibrium.

00:41:28.990 --> 00:41:29.490
OK.

00:41:29.490 --> 00:41:30.190
Those are good questions.

00:41:30.190 --> 00:41:31.820
We've gotten a little ahead of
what I wanted to talk about.

00:41:31.820 --> 00:41:33.882
So for now I'm just
imagining a free photon gas,

00:41:33.882 --> 00:41:35.340
which is an excellent
approximation

00:41:35.340 --> 00:41:36.964
for the early universe.

00:41:36.964 --> 00:41:38.630
And those photons
just continue to exist

00:41:38.630 --> 00:41:41.300
as the universe expands,
so their number density

00:41:41.300 --> 00:41:44.401
falls off as 1 over a cubed.

00:41:44.401 --> 00:41:45.900
But there's another
affect that goes

00:41:45.900 --> 00:41:47.880
on which is that the
photons are redshifting.

00:41:47.880 --> 00:41:50.050
And we already know
about that, but now we're

00:41:50.050 --> 00:41:53.720
going to take it into account
in terms of the energy balances.

00:41:53.720 --> 00:42:00.710
So we know that the frequency
of a photon at some time t2

00:42:00.710 --> 00:42:05.410
divide by its frequency
at some time t1,

00:42:05.410 --> 00:42:16.530
and here nu equals
frequency, is just

00:42:16.530 --> 00:42:19.820
diluted by the expansion
of the universe.

00:42:19.820 --> 00:42:22.040
This ratio is 1
over 1 plus z, where

00:42:22.040 --> 00:42:27.050
z is the redshift
between these two times.

00:42:27.050 --> 00:42:30.670
But written out in
more detail which

00:42:30.670 --> 00:42:32.880
is a formula we'll
actually be using,

00:42:32.880 --> 00:42:36.240
is just a of t1
divided by a of t2.

00:42:39.660 --> 00:42:42.290
When the scale factor doubles,
all the frequency is half.

00:42:45.180 --> 00:42:47.200
And that means that all
the photons are lowering

00:42:47.200 --> 00:42:52.026
in frequency, and we also know
that photons are quantized.

00:43:03.160 --> 00:43:05.850
The energy of a photon
can't be any old thing,

00:43:05.850 --> 00:43:12.620
but in fact, the energy of a
photon is equal to h times nu.

00:43:35.550 --> 00:43:37.705
Where little h is what's
called Planck's constant.

00:43:46.770 --> 00:43:51.420
And numerically there
are various units

00:43:51.420 --> 00:43:56.950
you could express it
in, but it's 4.136 times

00:43:56.950 --> 00:44:01.875
10 to the minus 15th
electron volt seconds.

00:44:05.360 --> 00:44:07.620
So if you measure a
frequency an inverse seconds,

00:44:07.620 --> 00:44:09.875
you get an energy in electron
volts from that formula.

00:44:17.040 --> 00:44:19.475
The important thing
for now though is

00:44:19.475 --> 00:44:24.440
that this says that the
energy of each photon-- being

00:44:24.440 --> 00:44:26.690
proportional to its frequency,
and the frequency being

00:44:26.690 --> 00:44:29.760
proportional to 1 over
the scale factor--

00:44:29.760 --> 00:44:34.950
the energy of each photons is
proportional to 1 over a of t.

00:44:39.820 --> 00:44:41.620
And then the total
energy density

00:44:41.620 --> 00:44:44.610
of photons in
photon on gas which

00:44:44.610 --> 00:44:48.360
I'll call u sub gamma, the
energy density of the gas,

00:44:48.360 --> 00:44:51.940
can be thought of as the
number density of photons

00:44:51.940 --> 00:44:55.440
times the energy of each photon.

00:44:55.440 --> 00:44:57.150
And the number
density is falling off

00:44:57.150 --> 00:45:01.180
like 1 over a cubed, the energy
is falling off like 1 over a.

00:45:01.180 --> 00:45:04.170
And therefore, this
is proportional to 1

00:45:04.170 --> 00:45:05.500
over a to the fourth.

00:45:12.780 --> 00:45:16.020
So as the universe
expands, the density

00:45:16.020 --> 00:45:19.230
of non-relativistic matter
falls off like 1 over a cubed--

00:45:19.230 --> 00:45:22.060
as we've been talking
about some time now--

00:45:22.060 --> 00:45:24.550
but the energy of
radiation falls off faster,

00:45:24.550 --> 00:45:26.110
like 1 over a to
the fourth because

00:45:26.110 --> 00:45:27.568
of the red shifting
of the photons.

00:45:55.820 --> 00:46:00.170
OK, now once we know
this, we can ask ourselves

00:46:00.170 --> 00:46:03.920
what happens if we look at
our universe going backwards,

00:46:03.920 --> 00:46:07.440
knowing where we are
now where we come from?

00:46:07.440 --> 00:46:10.340
And if the energy
density of photons

00:46:10.340 --> 00:46:15.630
is falling off faster than
the energy density of matter,

00:46:15.630 --> 00:46:17.750
it would mean that the
ratio is getting smaller

00:46:17.750 --> 00:46:19.722
as we go forward in time.

00:46:19.722 --> 00:46:21.430
But that of course
implies that the ratio

00:46:21.430 --> 00:46:24.397
gets larger as we go
backwards in time.

00:46:24.397 --> 00:46:26.230
So as we go backwards
in time, the radiation

00:46:26.230 --> 00:46:28.610
becomes more and more
important, and there actually

00:46:28.610 --> 00:46:32.590
is going to be a time when the
radiation will equal the matter

00:46:32.590 --> 00:46:36.390
and at earlier times the
radiation will dominate.

00:46:36.390 --> 00:46:41.300
Today I'll just give
you a number for now,

00:46:41.300 --> 00:46:42.990
we'll learn later
how to calculate it,

00:46:42.990 --> 00:46:46.440
but for today the
total radiation energy

00:46:46.440 --> 00:46:54.100
density in the universe
is equal to 7.01 times 10

00:46:54.100 --> 00:46:57.885
to the minus 14 joules
per meter cubed.

00:47:07.162 --> 00:47:09.245
And this actually includes
two kinds of radiation,

00:47:09.245 --> 00:47:14.980
it includes photons
and also neutrinos,

00:47:14.980 --> 00:47:17.220
which at least in
the early universe

00:47:17.220 --> 00:47:20.057
behaved just like radiation.

00:47:20.057 --> 00:47:22.640
And we'll be talking more about
neutrinos later so don't worry

00:47:22.640 --> 00:47:25.820
if you don't have any
idea what a neutrino is.

00:47:29.240 --> 00:47:32.090
But for now it's just another
contribution to the radiation,

00:47:32.090 --> 00:47:34.494
and we can measure
basically this is all

00:47:34.494 --> 00:47:35.910
based on measuring
the temperature

00:47:35.910 --> 00:47:38.007
of the cosmic microwave
background radiation--

00:47:38.007 --> 00:47:40.090
and we'll learn later how
to make that conversion.

00:47:40.090 --> 00:47:41.140
But once you measure
the temperature

00:47:41.140 --> 00:47:42.530
of the cosmic
background radiation

00:47:42.530 --> 00:47:45.010
and have a theory about how
many neutrinos there should be,

00:47:45.010 --> 00:47:46.718
that's actually all
theoretical and we'll

00:47:46.718 --> 00:47:48.320
talk about that later as well.

00:47:48.320 --> 00:47:49.730
One can determine
what the energy

00:47:49.730 --> 00:47:54.310
density of that radiation is.

00:47:54.310 --> 00:48:02.270
And it corresponds to a mass
density just dividing by C

00:48:02.270 --> 00:48:13.030
squared of 7.80 times 10 to the
minus 31 kilograms per meter

00:48:13.030 --> 00:48:14.234
cubed.

00:48:14.234 --> 00:48:15.650
And when I think
of mass densities

00:48:15.650 --> 00:48:19.020
I always like to think of in
centimeters per-- excuse me,

00:48:19.020 --> 00:48:21.684
grams per centimeter
cubed because I'm

00:48:21.684 --> 00:48:24.100
used to the density of water
being one gram per centimeter

00:48:24.100 --> 00:48:26.420
cubed and I like to be able
to make that comparison.

00:48:26.420 --> 00:48:31.220
So just making that conversion,
usually I use SI units,

00:48:31.220 --> 00:48:35.090
but some things just seem to
make more sense in other units.

00:48:35.090 --> 00:48:41.026
So it's 10 to the minus 34
grams per centimeter cubed,

00:48:41.026 --> 00:48:44.270
so 10 to the minus 34, or
maybe 10 to the minus 33,

00:48:44.270 --> 00:48:47.260
times the density of water.

00:48:47.260 --> 00:48:50.130
And this is incredibly
low even compared

00:48:50.130 --> 00:48:53.260
to the critical density
of our universe,

00:48:53.260 --> 00:48:54.710
and the actual
density we know is

00:48:54.710 --> 00:48:57.020
very near this critical density.

00:48:57.020 --> 00:48:59.800
Let me remind you that
the critical density

00:48:59.800 --> 00:49:03.180
we derived a formula for,
and when we put numbers

00:49:03.180 --> 00:49:05.050
into that formula
we found that was

00:49:05.050 --> 00:49:10.310
equal to 1.88 times
little h0 squared,

00:49:10.310 --> 00:49:13.670
which is Hubble's units--
Hubble's constant in units

00:49:13.670 --> 00:49:17.820
of 100 kilometers per
second per megaparsec--

00:49:17.820 --> 00:49:21.830
I'll write that in
a second-- times 10

