01:06:18.080 --> 01:06:23.680
is equal to some constant,
b, divided by a cubed of t.

01:06:23.680 --> 01:06:25.890
And this we know how
to differentiate.

01:06:25.890 --> 01:06:29.850
We can write Rho dot is
equal to minus b over a

01:06:29.850 --> 01:06:33.050
to the fourth of t times a dot.

01:06:36.810 --> 01:06:41.060
And that is equal to minus 3.

01:06:41.060 --> 01:06:43.360
I'm sorry--there's a 3 here.

01:06:43.360 --> 01:06:48.130
Minus 3 times a dot over
a times the original RHO.

01:06:52.130 --> 01:06:53.860
So we can forget the
intermediate steps,

01:06:53.860 --> 01:06:56.860
and we just arrived
at the equation

01:06:56.860 --> 01:07:01.756
that RHO dot is equal to minus
3 a dot over a times RHO.

01:07:01.756 --> 01:07:03.380
And we can think of
that as going along

01:07:03.380 --> 01:07:05.630
with equations one and two.

01:07:05.630 --> 01:07:07.850
Maybe I'll even
give that a number.

01:07:07.850 --> 01:07:10.770
Equation three
will be RHO dot is

01:07:10.770 --> 01:07:15.285
equal to minus 3 a
dot over a times RHO.

01:07:18.850 --> 01:07:21.970
Now for radiation,
there will be a 4 here.

01:07:21.970 --> 01:07:24.540
The 4 will arrive the same
way as the 3 arrives there.

01:07:24.540 --> 01:07:28.740
It's just the power that
appeared in the factor of a.

01:07:28.740 --> 01:07:30.540
So for radiation, this
last formula we know

01:07:30.540 --> 01:07:33.480
is going to be modified,
which is the key point.

01:07:33.480 --> 01:07:35.920
Note that these three
formulas are not

01:07:35.920 --> 01:07:38.750
independent of each other.

01:07:38.750 --> 01:07:42.050
If we know, for example,
equation one, which

01:07:42.050 --> 01:07:44.006
is an equation for
a dot, we could

01:07:44.006 --> 01:07:45.630
differentiate that
with respect to time

01:07:45.630 --> 01:07:47.980
and get an equation
for a double dot.

01:07:47.980 --> 01:07:51.120
When we do that, everything
has to be differentiated.

01:07:51.120 --> 01:07:53.390
So it involves
differentiating a,

01:07:53.390 --> 01:07:57.170
but that just expresses things
in terms of derivatives of a.

01:07:57.170 --> 01:07:59.980
But the new quantity that
gets introduced is RHO.

01:07:59.980 --> 01:08:02.570
If we wanted to differentiate
this equation with respect

01:08:02.570 --> 01:08:06.300
to time, we have to
know what RHO dot is.

01:08:06.300 --> 01:08:07.130
But we do.

01:08:07.130 --> 01:08:09.850
That's what equation
three tells us.

01:08:09.850 --> 01:08:13.620
So we can differentiate equation
one, use equation three,

01:08:13.620 --> 01:08:15.661
and we can derive an
equation for a double dot.

01:08:15.661 --> 01:08:17.244
And if these equations
are consistent,

01:08:17.244 --> 01:08:18.500
it'd better be equation two.

01:08:18.500 --> 01:08:19.279
And it will be.

01:08:19.279 --> 01:08:21.500
You can check it.

01:08:21.500 --> 01:08:23.790
And actually, I think any
two of these equations

01:08:23.790 --> 01:08:25.760
can be used to derive the third.

01:08:25.760 --> 01:08:27.414
Those equations
just are-- really

01:08:27.414 --> 01:08:28.830
a set of two
independent equations

01:08:28.830 --> 01:08:30.640
and one dependent equation.

01:08:30.640 --> 01:08:35.210
You can shuffle it
any way you want.

01:08:35.210 --> 01:08:39.340
But, now what we want
to do is to consider

01:08:39.340 --> 01:08:40.779
a different kind of matter.

01:08:40.779 --> 01:08:42.380
Instead of
non-relativistic matter,

01:08:42.380 --> 01:08:45.569
we're considering photon matter.

01:08:45.569 --> 01:08:47.210
And in particular,
we know that it's

01:08:47.210 --> 01:08:48.615
going to change equation three.

01:08:56.939 --> 01:09:01.220
So for radiation,
3 gets modified

01:09:01.220 --> 01:09:10.620
into 3 prime, which
is the equation that

01:09:10.620 --> 01:09:16.890
says that RHO dot is equal to
minus 4 a dot over a times RHO.

01:09:36.630 --> 01:09:41.010
So how are we going to
fix these equations?

01:09:41.010 --> 01:09:43.080
Now they're inconsistent.

01:09:43.080 --> 01:09:46.521
If we change three and don't
change either one or two,

01:09:46.521 --> 01:09:48.520
we know that we're
inconsistent, because any two

01:09:48.520 --> 01:09:51.649
of those equations can be
used to derive the third.

01:09:51.649 --> 01:09:53.210
So we're in trouble.

01:09:53.210 --> 01:09:55.230
Either equations
one or two will also

01:09:55.230 --> 01:09:58.260
have to be modified if we're
going to modify equation three.

01:10:15.660 --> 01:10:16.160
OK.

01:10:16.160 --> 01:10:20.040
Before we go on, I'd like to
say a little more about why

01:10:20.040 --> 01:10:23.032
this equation is different
from that equation.

01:10:23.032 --> 01:10:24.490
One might think
that it should just

01:10:24.490 --> 01:10:26.412
be governed by the
conservation of energy.

01:10:26.412 --> 01:10:28.120
After all, we just
write down an equation

01:10:28.120 --> 01:10:32.540
for RHO dot-- how energy
density changes with time.

01:10:32.540 --> 01:10:35.030
Shouldn't conservation
of energy determine that?

01:10:35.030 --> 01:10:36.850
It does.

01:10:36.850 --> 01:10:39.660
But there is an extra element
to conservation of energy

01:10:39.660 --> 01:10:42.950
that we need to
take into account,

01:10:42.950 --> 01:10:45.540
and that is the pressure
of the gas affects

01:10:45.540 --> 01:10:48.510
what happens to its
energy as it expands.

01:10:48.510 --> 01:10:50.470
So before we get back
to the early universe,

01:10:50.470 --> 01:10:52.680
I just want to consider a
gas in a piston chamber.

01:10:56.180 --> 01:11:01.990
And I'm going to let the piston
have an area a, and inside

01:11:01.990 --> 01:11:05.750
we're going to have a volume
v. Just to define our notation.

01:11:09.260 --> 01:11:11.340
If we have a gas
inside a piston chamber

01:11:11.340 --> 01:11:15.390
and let the piston chamber
enlarge by pulling out

01:11:15.390 --> 01:11:21.330
on the piston, the gas has
a pressure, in general,

01:11:21.330 --> 01:11:24.570
and that pressure will
exert a force on the piston.

01:11:24.570 --> 01:11:27.910
So if I allow the piston
to move to the right,

01:11:27.910 --> 01:11:30.150
that gas will be
exerting a force

01:11:30.150 --> 01:11:32.680
on the piston in the
direction that it's moving.

01:11:32.680 --> 01:11:35.920
And that means the gas will
be doing work on the piston.

01:11:35.920 --> 01:11:39.080
So, by our ordinary notions
of Newtonian conservation

01:11:39.080 --> 01:11:43.310
of energy, we would know that
the gas would lose energy,

01:11:43.310 --> 01:11:47.490
and we can even calculate
how much energy it loses.

01:11:47.490 --> 01:11:51.870
And the formula is easy enough
to get in a Newtonian context.

01:11:51.870 --> 01:11:55.280
It's just du is equal
to minus the pressure

01:11:55.280 --> 01:11:58.970
of the gas times the
change in volume.

01:11:58.970 --> 01:12:00.550
A famous formula.

01:12:00.550 --> 01:12:02.550
And this just comes
about by saying

01:12:02.550 --> 01:12:06.040
that the work that's done is
the force times the distance.

01:12:06.040 --> 01:12:08.850
The force is the
pressure times the area.

01:12:08.850 --> 01:12:12.710
And the volume is the
area times the distance.

01:12:12.710 --> 01:12:14.460
And putting those
things together,

01:12:14.460 --> 01:12:16.204
you get this
formula immediately.

01:12:16.204 --> 01:12:18.120
Now this formula is
actually much more general

01:12:18.120 --> 01:12:21.310
than the quasi derivation
that I just showed.

01:12:21.310 --> 01:12:23.750
It works no matter what
the shape of the gas is.

01:12:23.750 --> 01:12:25.740
If you put a gas in
any kind of a container

01:12:25.740 --> 01:12:31.560
and let that container enlarge,
even in an irregular way,

01:12:31.560 --> 01:12:33.770
the work that the gas
will do will always

01:12:33.770 --> 01:12:35.620
be equal to minus the
pressure of the gas

01:12:35.620 --> 01:12:39.144
times the change in the volume.

01:12:39.144 --> 01:12:40.810
We can apply this to
the early universe.

01:12:40.810 --> 01:12:43.780
It actually works.

01:12:43.780 --> 01:12:45.455
The difference
between our two cases

01:12:45.455 --> 01:12:48.696
is that our non-relativistic
matter has no pressure at all.

01:12:48.696 --> 01:12:50.820
We're just talking about
particles sitting at rest.

01:12:50.820 --> 01:12:52.420
They're not bouncing
off of any walls.

01:12:52.420 --> 01:12:54.249
They're not creating
any pressure,

01:12:54.249 --> 01:12:56.290
while the photons are
moving around all the time.

01:12:56.290 --> 01:12:57.820
And if you imagine
a box of them,

01:12:57.820 --> 01:12:59.820
they'd be hitting against
the walls of that box,

01:12:59.820 --> 01:13:00.680
exerting a pressure.

01:13:05.990 --> 01:13:08.170
And we're now in a position
to relate the pressure

01:13:08.170 --> 01:13:11.460
to the difference between
the 3's and the 4's that

01:13:11.460 --> 01:13:15.955
appear in those two equations
for RHO dot in the two cases.

01:13:22.000 --> 01:13:27.190
To apply this naive idea
to a piece of the universe,

01:13:27.190 --> 01:13:36.800
we can imagine choosing-- we're
going to choose some fixed

01:13:36.800 --> 01:13:42.370
volume in our co-moving
coordinate system.

01:13:53.842 --> 01:13:55.800
So our box, the volume
that we're talking about

01:13:55.800 --> 01:13:57.633
will actually be expanding
with the universe

01:13:57.633 --> 01:13:59.900
but be fixed in
co-moving coordinates.

01:13:59.900 --> 01:14:08.410
And the physical volume
therefore of our box

01:14:08.410 --> 01:14:13.590
will be a cubed of t times
the coordinate volume

01:14:13.590 --> 01:14:18.560
of the box-- the volume
and not just cubed.

01:14:18.560 --> 01:14:20.610
And this volume will
be independent of time.

01:14:20.610 --> 01:14:21.911
There's time dependents there.

01:14:21.911 --> 01:14:23.160
There's time dependents there.

01:14:23.160 --> 01:14:25.225
The physical volume of
our box will be enlarging.

01:14:28.870 --> 01:14:33.540
The total energy in our
box, the total gas energy,

01:14:33.540 --> 01:14:35.840
which I'll call
capital U, will just

01:14:35.840 --> 01:14:40.180
be the physical volume
times the energy density.

01:14:40.180 --> 01:14:42.530
The energy density is
energy per physical volume.

01:14:46.380 --> 01:14:50.660
And we can now
apply this formula

01:14:50.660 --> 01:14:55.000
using this U and this v.

01:14:55.000 --> 01:14:57.076
And here again is one
of these cases where

01:14:57.076 --> 01:14:58.950
I'm going to be skipping
steps because you're

01:14:58.950 --> 01:15:01.160
going to be doing it in
detail on the homework.

01:15:01.160 --> 01:15:03.140
But by putting these
equations together,

01:15:03.140 --> 01:15:08.680
what you'll find is that d dt
of a cubed times RHO times c

01:15:08.680 --> 01:15:14.080
squared-- this is just d dt
of a cubed times the energy

01:15:14.080 --> 01:15:18.170
density-- basically,
the left hand side

01:15:18.170 --> 01:15:25.890
of that equation divided by dt
and divided by v coordinates--

01:15:25.890 --> 01:15:32.881
is equal to minus p
times d dt of a cubed.

01:15:32.881 --> 01:15:35.130
And this is just the PDV
term from the right hand side

01:15:35.130 --> 01:15:38.117
of that equation rewritten
in terms of the variables.

01:15:38.117 --> 01:15:39.700
And you'll be doing
this for homework.

01:15:39.700 --> 01:15:42.609
I'm just getting
straight the factors

01:15:42.609 --> 01:15:43.900
to make sure I have them right.

01:15:58.021 --> 01:15:58.520
OK.

01:15:58.520 --> 01:16:00.311
Reshuffling that
equation-- and again, this

01:16:00.311 --> 01:16:02.140
is a homework problem--
you can turn that

01:16:02.140 --> 01:16:04.590
into an equation for RHO dot.

01:16:04.590 --> 01:16:09.120
And what you'll get
is minus 3 a dot

01:16:09.120 --> 01:16:15.420
over a times RHO plus
p over c squared.

01:16:24.690 --> 01:16:27.110
And now we can see how
our two cases emerge.

01:16:27.110 --> 01:16:29.134
If the pressure is 0,
we get minus 3 a dot

01:16:29.134 --> 01:16:30.550
over 8 times RHO,
which is what we

01:16:30.550 --> 01:16:32.700
had for non-relativistic matter.

01:16:32.700 --> 01:16:34.660
And the photon gas is
going to have a pressure,

01:16:34.660 --> 01:16:36.285
and we could read
off from this formula

01:16:36.285 --> 01:16:39.370
to know what the pressure has
to be to turn the 3 into a 4.

01:16:39.370 --> 01:16:44.290
The pressure has to be
a factor of a third.

01:16:44.290 --> 01:16:46.810
So you determine for this
that the pressure for light

01:16:46.810 --> 01:16:53.050
is 1/3 of the energy density,
or 1/3 times RHO c squared.

01:16:53.050 --> 01:16:55.869
And that's what you need
to turn the 3 into a 4.

01:16:55.869 --> 01:16:57.910
So we now have indirectly
calculated the pressure

01:16:57.910 --> 01:17:00.076
of light, and this agrees
with any other calculation

01:17:00.076 --> 01:17:03.090
for the pressure of
light that you might do.

01:17:03.090 --> 01:17:05.670
It's by no means the
only way to calculate it.

01:17:05.670 --> 01:17:09.060
And now finally,
we're in a position--

01:17:09.060 --> 01:17:11.200
and we'll just do
this quickly to decide

01:17:11.200 --> 01:17:13.920
how to modify these equations.

01:17:13.920 --> 01:17:16.690
Now, we're not in a position
to determine that rigorously.

01:17:16.690 --> 01:17:20.410
It can be determined rigorously
by doing general relativity,

01:17:20.410 --> 01:17:23.800
which we're not
doing at that level.

01:17:23.800 --> 01:17:26.690
But we can still
motivate the answer.

01:17:26.690 --> 01:17:28.360
One of these two
equations is going

01:17:28.360 --> 01:17:30.850
to have to be changed
to accommodate

01:17:30.850 --> 01:17:34.470
a more general
expression for RHO dot.

01:17:34.470 --> 01:17:36.740
The top equation
we know is really

01:17:36.740 --> 01:17:39.030
an equation for
conservation of energy.

01:17:39.030 --> 01:17:41.930
That's how we got it
in the Newtonian case

01:17:41.930 --> 01:17:46.110
where little k ended up
being partial to the energy

01:17:46.110 --> 01:17:47.640
in the Newtonian case.

01:17:47.640 --> 01:17:49.140
But this is basically
a conservation

01:17:49.140 --> 01:17:50.440
of energy equation.

01:17:50.440 --> 01:17:52.120
And that's what you
expect, just given

01:17:52.120 --> 01:17:54.290
your general notion
of mechanics as well.

01:17:54.290 --> 01:17:57.560
If you have a second
order equation,

01:17:57.560 --> 01:17:59.930
a second order differential
is with respect to time.

01:17:59.930 --> 01:18:01.110
That's the force equation.

01:18:01.110 --> 01:18:02.860
And if you have a first
order differential

01:18:02.860 --> 01:18:06.010
equation with respect to time,
1/2 mv squared plus v of r

01:18:06.010 --> 01:18:07.070
equals constant.

01:18:07.070 --> 01:18:09.300
That's energy conservation.

01:18:09.300 --> 01:18:10.250
Same thing here.

01:18:10.250 --> 01:18:13.910
And we know that energy
cannot suddenly change.

01:18:13.910 --> 01:18:18.780
If we imagine-- I guess the
first experiment I want to do

01:18:18.780 --> 01:18:20.730
is imagining somehow
there's an explosion

01:18:20.730 --> 01:18:22.920
throughout all of space.

01:18:22.920 --> 01:18:27.670
I imagine putting pieces
of TNT throughout space

01:18:27.670 --> 01:18:30.560
and arranging for, at the same
cosmic time, for all of them

01:18:30.560 --> 01:18:31.200
to be ignited.

01:18:31.200 --> 01:18:34.014
And that would suddenly change
the pressure of the universe,

01:18:34.014 --> 01:18:35.805
but it would not change
the energy density.

01:18:35.805 --> 01:18:38.662
The energy density
would be conserved.

01:18:38.662 --> 01:18:40.620
So the bottom line is
that pressures can change

01:18:40.620 --> 01:18:43.950
discontinuously, but
energy densities cannot.

01:18:43.950 --> 01:18:48.640
And since this equation is
the conservation of energy

01:18:48.640 --> 01:18:51.660
equation, we'd expected that
nothing can change suddenly

01:18:51.660 --> 01:18:54.050
here, that the pressure
term cannot contribute here,

01:18:54.050 --> 01:18:56.574
because if it did, the pressure
term would changed suddenly.

01:18:56.574 --> 01:18:58.740
Nothing else in this equation
would change suddenly.

01:18:58.740 --> 01:19:01.350
There would be no way the
equation could be satisfied.

01:19:01.350 --> 01:19:05.130
But if we added a pressure
term to the second equation,

01:19:05.130 --> 01:19:08.900
that would allow the pressure
to change discontinuously

01:19:08.900 --> 01:19:10.135
as the TNT went off.

01:19:10.135 --> 01:19:12.260
And that would change a
double dot discontinuously.

01:19:12.260 --> 01:19:14.530
And there's nothing wrong
with a double dot changing

01:19:14.530 --> 01:19:15.350
discontinuously.

01:19:15.350 --> 01:19:17.780
If you suddenly the apply
a new force to a particle,

01:19:17.780 --> 01:19:21.350
you suddenly change its second
derivative of its motion.

01:19:21.350 --> 01:19:23.500
You suddenly change
its acceleration.

01:19:23.500 --> 01:19:24.510
So that's OK.

01:19:24.510 --> 01:19:26.690
So any pressure to
this term make sense.

01:19:26.690 --> 01:19:29.490
Adding pressure to this
equation does not make sense.

01:19:29.490 --> 01:19:31.370
And then we can just
ask, what do you

01:19:31.370 --> 01:19:33.910
have to do to this equation if
we're going to add a pressure

01:19:33.910 --> 01:19:36.280
term to make all
three equations now

01:19:36.280 --> 01:19:40.220
consistent with the new
equation for RHO dot?

01:19:40.220 --> 01:19:42.970
It's your homework problem
to answer that question,

01:19:42.970 --> 01:19:44.949
but the homework
tells you the answer,

01:19:44.949 --> 01:19:46.990
and I'll write the answer
on the board right now,

01:19:46.990 --> 01:19:50.830
and then we'll consider
today's lecture over.

01:19:50.830 --> 01:19:57.840
The bottom line is that
equation number one

01:19:57.840 --> 01:20:02.750
has to be modified
into one prime, which

01:20:02.750 --> 01:20:05.930
says that equation number
two has to be modified.

01:20:05.930 --> 01:20:06.960
What am I talking about?

01:20:13.570 --> 01:20:17.890
And the new equation
is a double dot

01:20:17.890 --> 01:20:23.600
is equal to minus 4
pi over 3 G times RHO

01:20:23.600 --> 01:20:28.880
plus 3p over c squared times a.

01:20:34.140 --> 01:20:37.070
And now we have a consistent
set of Friedman equations,

01:20:37.070 --> 01:20:38.570
and these are the
Friedman equations

01:20:38.570 --> 01:20:40.790
that we would have gotten
if we had done everything

01:20:40.790 --> 01:20:43.330
using general relativity
from the beginning.

